snippet.textDisplay:
Original: he's still high and infuriated that he's managed to fall, hook, line and sinker, for that woman who made him chase that addictive bittersweetness only she could offer knowing full well it was tearing him apart. He was potentially fascinated by how she made him feel and that's what helped keep him hooked.

Reimagined: he's in agony. He relised she's hurt him and he's beating himself up for falling for something he knew was terrible. He knows it could kill him and he's broken that he allowed her to become his drug and at the very end-he's pissed that she is the way she is.

My conclusion? I love both versions of this song, the direction, colours, setting and feel through out the video is almost addicting in itself. I'm just upset you kept that singing voice and piano skills from us for so long!
snippet.textOriginal:
Original: he's still high and infuriated that he's managed to fall, hook, line and sinker, for that woman who made him chase that addictive bittersweetness only she could offer knowing full well it was tearing him apart. Reimagined: he's in agony. He relised she's hurt him and he's beating himself up for falling for something he knew was terrible. He knows it could kill him and he's broken that he allowed her to become his drug and at the very end-he's pissed that she is the way she is.

My conclusion? I love both versions of this song, the direction, colours, setting and feel through out the video is almost addicting in itself. I'm just upset you kept that singing voice and piano skills from us for so long!
